text: Sounds like Dangerfield. I don't have any Charlie Sheen stories but I don't care what the man did in his personal life he's still one of my favorites and the original two and a half Men still one of the funniest shows ever put on TV. If I have to make a comment that you might recognize I'll say this. I'm a full-blooded Italian born in the Bronx. Move to North Carolina when I was 11 so I was raised in the South by with these rednecks. And back in those days in the late seventies early eighties there was a lot of rednecks. I don't know whether to sing amor or whistle Dixie. Was that funny. I had a New York City accent from the Bronx Italian. First year in North Carolina 1978 first day of school I had one month of the fifth grade left. A girl came up to me and asked me what country I was from because of my accent. I said I'm from New York that's in this country. My accent was so strong the next year in school they put me in speech class. After about a week the teacher said this guy doesn't have a speech impediment he has a New York City accent. I'm the world's only Bronx Italian redneck. When I go back back to New York City to visit my people. They hear my accent which is Southern now according to them they asked me what part of Texas I'm from.
